review_blob: If you like fin du monde or delirium tremens, consider this a somewhat lighter version and, as with those others well, anytime, any place.
This is good enough to pull me away from Erdinger, not to mention Hacker and Paulaner. Summer could be as hazy as the color of this beauty.
I defy anyone to find me a better dark ale. This has a stunning nut and smoke finish with a slight sweetness that reminds you that life is too short to be drinking cheap nut brown ale.
As far as white beer goes, this is tough to beat. I place it ahead of Paulaner and just slightly better than Hacker...
This is possibly the best Trappist style ale one can enjoy. I place this up there with the likes of Delerium, even though this is richer overall.
